![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/3b4f39a4-83fa-4eb9-bcd1-9b81fcb1f72b/310.jpg)

Batman: Mask of The Phantasm is 30 years old! Released on December 25, 1993, Phantasm holds the distinction of being the first animated _Batman_ film to be given a theatrical release. Unfortunately, because of the film's scant promotion, it underperformed at the box-office and it would be close to 25 years until an animated Batman graced the silver screen again. Join us as we look back fondly at this film, debate its talking points and just gush over the style of Batman the animated series.

  
Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  

